Torrential rain in Johannesburg has been flooding roads since the early hours of Saturday morning. JOHANNESBURG - Torrential rain in Johannesburg has been flooding roads since the early hours of Saturday morning. This, combined with load-shedding, seems to be a recipe for disaster. JMPD spokesperson Wayne Minnaar warned that the M1 North and South double-decker freeway has been blocked off. SURVIVAL GUIDE: What to do in a flash flood Minnaar said several roads in Johannesburg has flooded "We want to urge motorists to exercise extreme caution." He said officers are monitoring roads crossing rivers.